comments.text: Bit inaccurate because Foden has been playing much deeper as left center mid for the majority of this season and has been top. Pep only started to start him on the wing and let him go inside in the recent two games to bring him closer to the box for his output, hence the goals, at the cost of losing some of the control he provides playing deep. comments.text:
People always make it sound like Foden fell out of the sky in 2023 and suddenly had a word class season. He was good before that, too, you know. 
There's a reason Foden, at the age of 18, started important PL matches in the title race against Liverpool in 18/19 and scored match winners while Cole Palmer couldn't break through until he left age 21. 
Just look at the treble season (year before his PFA season). He was _incredible..._ until a foot injury followed up by an appendectomy sidelined him for a while after which he couldn't break through into the best XI of that season anymore because it was set. 
Still brilliantly assisted the fourth against Madrid minutes after coming on and was one of City's best players in the UCL Final after coming on for KDB
